# CI/CD Workflow Conventions

## Existing Workflows
| File | Trigger | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| `backend.yml` | Push/PR to main, `backend-api/**` | Go build, vet, gofmt, unit + integration tests |
| `frontend.yml` | Push/PR to main, `frontend/**` | Flutter format, analyze, test |
| `pr-review.yml` | PR opened/synchronized | Claude AI auto-review + PR description |
| `deploy.yml` | Push to main, `backend-api/**` | SSH deploy, systemctl restart |

## Backend CI Requirements
- Go 1.23 with Redis service container
- Must pass: `go build`, `go vet`, `gofmt` check, `go test`
- Integration tests require Redis on port 6379

## Frontend CI Requirements
- Flutter stable channel
- Must pass: `dart format --set-exit-if-changed`, `flutter analyze`, `flutter test`
- Test failures should be documented, not hidden

## Rules
- Never skip CI checks or add `[skip ci]` without team agreement
- All new endpoints need corresponding test coverage
- Swagger docs auto-regenerate via pre-commit hook — don't manually edit `docs/`
- Deploy workflow only triggers on `main` branch pushes to `backend-api/`
